# Graphify exclusion list — per C21a (2026-05-23 brain-refinement Stage 7).
#
# graphify reads ONLY this file at the scan root (not nested .graphifyignore
# files); when this file exists, .gitignore at the same level is NOT read
# by graphify. So this file enumerates everything we want excluded from the
# structural graph — both the git-noise patterns (mirrored from .gitignore)
# and the graphify-specific extras.

# ---- mirrored from .gitignore (keep in sync) ----
node_modules/
dist/
_logs/
_queue/
_worktrees/
_review/
# Excludes /projects/* (managed projects), NOT brain/projects/<name>/themes/
# (per-project sub-wikis — load-bearing). Graphify's matcher tests every
# path COMPONENT against the pattern, so a bare `projects/` would catch
# both `/projects` AND `/brain/projects` — a real bug. The `*` suffix
# anchors the pattern by requiring a slash-and-something following,
# which only matches the top-level `projects/<name>` form.
projects/*
benchmarks/*/results/
benchmarks/*/results-negatives/
benchmarks/*/results-judged/
benchmarks/*/fixtures/**/__pycache__/
benchmarks/*/fixtures/**/.pytest_cache/
benchmarks/*/fixtures/**/AGENT.md
benchmarks/*/fixtures/**/fix_plan.md
benchmarks/*/fixtures/**/PROMPT.md
benchmarks/*/fixtures/**/.forge/
forge.config.json
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
.claude/*
!.claude/commands/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
brain/.obsidian/
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# ---- graphify-specific additions ----

# Frozen historical state — deliberately retained as evidence, not part of
# forge's live architecture.
brain/_archive/

# Raw sources — Karpathy Layer 1 (immutable provenance). Themes summarise
# these and link to them via `## Sources` markdown; the curated theme is the
# knowledge unit, raw is the provenance trail. Including raw in the graph
# would create leaf-cross-link noise (each cycle archive cross-referencing
# every other) when the operator's intent is a tree: themes → raw is
# top-down provenance, raw ↔ raw is not a meaningful relationship.
brain/_raw/

# Bench fixtures are test inputs, not forge architecture. Bench harness
# code (cases.json, score.ts, scoring.ts, sdk.ts at each bench root) IS
# in scope — only the fixtures/ subtree is excluded.
benchmarks/*/fixtures/

# Graphify's own output. The committed graph.json must not be re-walked
# into itself (would create huge JSON noise + self-references). The root
# symlink and the canonical path are both excluded.
graphify-out/
brain/graphify-out/

# Planning docs are EPHEMERAL — live during execution, then the durable
# outcomes are extracted as brain themes and the plan docs themselves are
# pruned. The "history of decision making is what informs future direction,
# not the specifics of plans themselves" (operator principle, 2026-05-23).
#
# Exclude PER-STAGE PLANS + COUNCIL DELIBERATIONS + EXEC SCAFFOLDING.
# KEEP the durable per-batch outcomes (CONTRACTS.md, *-CLOSURE.md,
# LEARNINGS-*.md) — these are NOT matched by any pattern below so they
# stay in the graph by default. (Note: gitignore semantics don't allow
# re-including via `!` once a parent dir is excluded, so we exclude by
# file pattern instead of by directory.)
docs/planning/*/[0-9]*.md
docs/planning/*/*.council.md
docs/planning/*/EXECUTION-PLAN.md
docs/planning/*/INDEX.md
docs/planning/*/S*-SUMMARY.md
docs/planning/*/S*-DECISIONS.md
docs/planning/*/S*-PROPOSALS.md

# Forge-root operator-pending stage decision scratch from the 2026-05-20
# batch — transitional artifacts pending operator cleanup. Excluded per the
# same ephemeral-planning principle.
/S*-DECISIONS.md
/S*-PROPOSALS.md
/S*-SUMMARY.md
